        "description": "The `equals()` method is used to compare the input value `x` with the stored values in `singletons`. However, this method is not guaranteed to work correctly for all types of `T`. If `T` is a custom type, it should override the `equals()` method to ensure proper comparison.",
        "location": "Line 57"
    },

    {
        "description": "The `probability()` method returns the probability of the exact value `x`. However, if `x` is not present in the `singletons` list, the method will return 0, which might not be the intended behavior. It could be more intuitive to return `Double.NaN` or throw an exception in such cases.",
        "location": "Line 52"
    },

    {
        "description": "The `getSamples()` method returns a new list of pairs with the same probabilities as the original list. However, if the probabilities are changed after creating the distribution, the changes will not be reflected in the returned list. To ensure consistency, the method should return an unmodifiable list or create a new list with the updated probabilities.",
        "location": "Lines 63-68"
    }

